---
description: Blade, Tailwind CSS, and jQuery frontend rules
globs:
  - "resources/views/**/*.blade.php"
  - "resources/js/**/*.js"
  - "resources/css/**/*.css"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Server-rendered Blade behavior is canonical.
- Core flows must work without JavaScript.
- Use semantic HTML and accessible labels.
- Use reusable Blade components for repeated UI.
- Use Tailwind CSS with a mobile-first approach.
- Use Vietnamese user-facing text.
- Escape user-controlled output with normal Blade syntax.
- Do not use inline JavaScript or inline event handlers.
- Bind jQuery through data attributes.
- jQuery may enhance filters, variants, and cart interactions but must not contain business rules.
- AJAX and non-AJAX flows must call the same backend logic.
- Provide loading, empty, success, and error states.

- Product images must follow `docs/IMAGE_STRATEGY.md`.
- Use the local placeholder when no image exists.
- Use a stable square container and `object-contain`.
- Use lazy loading for listing images.
- Do not query image relationships from Blade.
- Do not use external image hotlinks.

- Build a friendly customer layout with visible search, account, categories, and cart.
- Use Font Awesome Free for appropriate icons.
- Do not add another icon library.
- Icon-only controls require accessible names.
- Format prices consistently as Vietnamese đồng.
- Dynamically enhance variants, search, filters, cart, and checkout summary with jQuery.
- Authoritative prices and totals must come from Laravel responses.
- JavaScript-calculated amounts are previews only.
- Update cart badge and totals without full reload when practical.
- Keep SSR and form fallbacks.
- Do not install another JavaScript library without human approval.
